Key Match Events: France won 3-0 against Luxembourg with goals from Kolo (43'), Clauss (70'), and Mbappe (85').
Pre-Game Insights: France head coach Didier Deschamps will not have any of his three Real Madrid players at his disposal for the friendly against Luxembourg.
Ferland Mendy and Eduardo Camavinga were both starters in Real Madrid's Champions League final win and are given more time to recuperate.
Aurelien Tchouameni missed the Champions League final due to a foot injury and will not participate in the friendly against Luxembourg.
N'Golo Kante has been recalled and may start in the friendly against Luxembourg.
Adrien Rabiot and Warren Zaire-Emery are likely starters in midfield for France.
Ousmane Dembele, Olivier Giroud, and Kylian Mbappe are expected to form the attacking quartet alongside Antoine Griezmann.
Theo Hernandez is expected to start at left-back, with Jules Kounde on the right flank, and Benjamin Pavard and Dayot Upamecano in central defense.
